{
  "texts": [
    "11 aimed to minimize the cost function on IoT devices by providing an entry point for collecting data blocks from a group of IoT systems.",
    "Tuli et al.",
    "12 introduced a generic broker in a Blockchain-based architecture to distribute tasks among different fog devices, addressing the challenges of computational overhead.",
    "However, these approaches rely on centralized Blockchain-based architectures, leaving them vulnerable to cyber-attacks such as tampering and Denial-of-Service (DoS).",
    "This paper proposes a patient monitoring system combining SDN and Blockchain to control and secure healthcare data that saves and manages patients' medical data."
  ]
}